{"id":1123,"date":"2021-05-04T21:47:33","date_gmt":"2021-05-04T21:47:33","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/programming.sdarobotics.org\/?page_id=1123"},"modified":"2024-09-02T18:59:46","modified_gmt":"2024-09-02T18:59:46","slug":"assembling-the-turret","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/assembling-the-turret\/","title":{"rendered":"Assembling the Turret"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Attach the two <strong>Limit Switches<\/strong> to the top of the&nbsp;<strong>Turntable Bottom Plate<\/strong>&nbsp;using four 2-56 machine screws and four <strong>Limit Switch Spacers<\/strong> as shown below. Note the <strong>Limit Switch Spacers<\/strong> placed between the limit switch and the plate. Also pay attention to the orientation of the limit switches.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/MountLimitSwitches.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/MountLimitSwitches.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1954\" width=\"368\" height=\"348\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/MountLimitSwitches.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/MountLimitSwitches-300x284.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/MountLimitSwitches-150x142.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/MountLimitSwitches-768x726.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 368px) 100vw, 368px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Using the 4 <strong>Turntable Spacers<\/strong>, attach the&nbsp;<strong>Turntable Bering<\/strong>&nbsp;to the top of the plate with four 1\/2 inch 8-32 machine screws as shown below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/LazySusan.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/LazySusan.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1957\" width=\"371\" height=\"343\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/LazySusan.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/LazySusan-300x278.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/LazySusan-150x139.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/LazySusan-768x711.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 371px) 100vw, 371px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, attach the Turntable Bottom Plate to the Chassis. Use two 2-1\/2 inch 8-32 bolts on the front and two 2-1\/4 inch 8-32 bolts on the back as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis6.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1962\" width=\"473\" height=\"464\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis6.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis6-300x294.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis6-150x147.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis6-768x753.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 473px) 100vw, 473px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now attach the Pi Camera Bracket to the Pi Camera Mount using two 1\/4 inch 2-56 screws as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/CameraMount.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/CameraMount.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1959\" width=\"384\" height=\"237\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/CameraMount.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/CameraMount-300x185.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/CameraMount-150x93.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/CameraMount-768x475.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 384px) 100vw, 384px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next we will assemble the <strong>Pi Camera Module<\/strong>. Attach a 50 cm <strong>Pi Camera Cable<\/strong> to the&nbsp;camera and then insert four 2-56 machine screws as shown below. Here I have used nylon (plastic) nuts to fasten the screws. These will act a spacers between the camera and the mount. It is not essential that these be nuts, you can also just use plastic spacers but using nuts will make it easier to assemble. It is important that you do not use metal nuts as they might short out traces on the PC board.<\/p>\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n<p><\/p><center><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/PiCameraWithScrews2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-1145\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/PiCameraWithScrews2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"207\" height=\"190\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/PiCameraWithScrews2.jpg 632w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/PiCameraWithScrews2-300x275.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/PiCameraWithScrews2-150x138.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 207px) 100vw, 207px\" \/><\/a> <a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/PiCameraWithCable1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-1146\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/PiCameraWithCable1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"208\" height=\"195\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/PiCameraWithCable1.jpg 712w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/PiCameraWithCable1-300x281.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/PiCameraWithCable1-150x141.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 208px) 100vw, 208px\" \/><\/a><\/center><p><\/p>\n\n\n<p>Now mount the camera on the&nbsp;<strong>Pi Camera Mount<\/strong>&nbsp;as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/CameraMount2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/CameraMount2-794x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1961\" width=\"283\" height=\"365\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/CameraMount2-794x1024.jpg 794w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/CameraMount2-233x300.jpg 233w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/CameraMount2-150x193.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/CameraMount2-768x990.jpg 768w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/CameraMount2.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 283px) 100vw, 283px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, using a 4-40 tap, tap the two holes in the Turntable Gear as shown below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/TapTurntableGear.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/TapTurntableGear.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1170\" width=\"421\" height=\"117\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/TapTurntableGear.jpg 843w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/TapTurntableGear-300x84.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/TapTurntableGear-150x42.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/TapTurntableGear-768x215.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 421px) 100vw, 421px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Cut a 43.5 cm length of 6 mm wide, 2 mm pitch&nbsp;<strong>Timing Belt<\/strong>&nbsp;and punch or drill a hole in 4 mm from each end large enough to thread a 4-40 screw. The hole should be centered in the second grove from the end, as shown below.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/CableWithBolt.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/CableWithBolt-1024x496.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1172\" width=\"359\" height=\"173\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/CableWithBolt-1024x496.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/CableWithBolt-300x145.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/CableWithBolt-150x73.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/CableWithBolt-768x372.jpg 768w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/CableWithBolt.jpg 1272w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 359px) 100vw, 359px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now attach the timing belt to the Turntable Gear using two 1\/2 inch 4-40 bolts:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/TimingBelt.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/TimingBelt.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1965\" width=\"473\" height=\"406\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/TimingBelt.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/TimingBelt-300x258.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/TimingBelt-150x129.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/TimingBelt-768x660.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 473px) 100vw, 473px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now using 1 inch 8-32 bolts place the <strong>Turntable Plate<\/strong> onto the <strong>Turntable Bottom<\/strong> plate followed by the &nbsp;<strong>Turntable Gear<\/strong>&nbsp;as shown below. Note the direction of the<strong> <\/strong>gear&nbsp;and make sure that the point at which the belt is fastened to the gear is at the rear. Also make sure that the lip on the <strong>Turntable Gear<\/strong> is on top.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Turntable1Fixed.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Turntable1Fixed-1024x407.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2026\" width=\"494\" height=\"196\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Turntable1Fixed-1024x407.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Turntable1Fixed-300x119.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Turntable1Fixed-150x60.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Turntable1Fixed-768x305.jpg 768w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Turntable1Fixed.jpg 1283w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 494px) 100vw, 494px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Then position the <strong>Turntable Top Plate<\/strong> and the <strong>Pi Camera Mount<\/strong> as shown and fasten with lock nuts:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Turntable2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Turntable2.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1971\" width=\"488\" height=\"429\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Turntable2.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Turntable2-300x264.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Turntable2-150x132.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Turntable2-768x676.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 488px) 100vw, 488px\" \/><\/a><figcaption>binary comment<\/figcaption><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now cut one of the 10 cm <strong>LED Heat Sinks<\/strong> in half so you have a 5 cm piece. Then drill holes in the heat sink and attach the <strong>Green LED<\/strong> to the heat sink as shown below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/LEDMounted.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/LEDMounted.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1193\" width=\"326\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/LEDMounted.jpg 820w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/LEDMounted-300x184.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/LEDMounted-150x92.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/LEDMounted-768x472.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 326px) 100vw, 326px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next cut a 16 inch length of red and black 20 gauge wire and solder one end to the plus and minus terminals of the LED. Take care to solder the black wire to the minus terminal and the red wire to the positive terminal:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/LEDMountedWithWires.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/LEDMountedWithWires.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1195\" width=\"330\" height=\"190\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/LEDMountedWithWires.jpg 940w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/LEDMountedWithWires-300x174.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/LEDMountedWithWires-150x87.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/LEDMountedWithWires-768x444.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 330px) 100vw, 330px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Then slide the heat sink into the slot on the <strong>Pi Camera Mount<\/strong> as shown below. Note the zip-tie attached to the top.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Light.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"htt\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Light.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1975\" width=\"491\" height=\"367\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Light.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Light-300x225.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Light-150x112.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Light-768x575.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 491px) 100vw, 491px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Tap the four holes in the <strong>Flywheel Mount<\/strong> as shown below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMountTap.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMountTap.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2009\" width=\"483\" height=\"434\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMountTap.png 754w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMountTap-300x269.png 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMountTap-150x135.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 483px) 100vw, 483px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now attach the <strong>Shooter Motor<\/strong> to the <strong>Shooter Mount<\/strong> using three 3mm M2.5 screws as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMount.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMount.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1978\" width=\"495\" height=\"591\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMount.jpg 857w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMount-251x300.jpg 251w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMount-150x179.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMount-768x918.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 495px) 100vw, 495px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Then attach the two<strong> Beam Break Sensors<\/strong> using two 4-40 bolts as shown. Note that the sensor with three wires goes on the left:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMount2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMount2.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1981\" width=\"502\" height=\"429\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMount2.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMount2-300x257.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMount2-150x128.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMount2-768x657.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 502px) 100vw, 502px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now we need to prepare the wiring cables which will connect the motors and sensors on the turret with the electronics on the chassis. We want to do this now because we will need to feed those cables down to the chassis and it will be easier to do this now rather than later.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>For the <strong>Shooter Motor<\/strong> we will need a 4 wire cable to read the quadrature encoder as well as a 2 wire cable for the motor power. Cut an 18 inch length of four conductor 28 gauge ribbon wire and a 16 inch length of 24 gauge red and black power wire. Then crimp connectors on each end of the two cables as shown below. Take particular care to connect the wires in the correct order as show:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterCables.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterCables.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1985\" width=\"504\" height=\"501\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterCables.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterCables-150x149.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterCables-768x765.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 504px) 100vw, 504px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>I highly recommend that you label both ends of the cables so that you can identify which cable is which later when connecting the wiring to the electronics.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now for the <strong>Feeder Motor<\/strong> cut a 18 inch section of 4 wire 28 gauge ribbon wire and a 16 inch section of 24 gauge red and black power wire. Then crimp connectors onto either end taking care of the order of the wires as shown below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/FeederWiring.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/FeederWiring-1022x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1992\" width=\"503\" height=\"503\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/FeederWiring-1022x1024.jpg 1022w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/FeederWiring-300x300.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/FeederWiring-150x150.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/FeederWiring-768x770.jpg 768w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/FeederWiring.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 503px) 100vw, 503px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>For the <strong>Beam Break Sensor<\/strong>, cut an 18 inch three wire 28 gauge ribbon wire and an 18 inch two wire 28 gauge ribbon wire. Attach connectors to each end of the cables taking care to make sure of the order as shown below;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/BeamBreakWiring-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/BeamBreakWiring-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2000\" width=\"496\" height=\"423\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/BeamBreakWiring-1.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/BeamBreakWiring-1-300x256.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/BeamBreakWiring-1-150x128.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/BeamBreakWiring-1-768x656.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 496px) 100vw, 496px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now feed the camera cable, the light power wire and all of the cables you just made through the hole on the side of the <strong>Shooter Mount<\/strong> and down through the hole on the <strong>Turntable Plate<\/strong>. Then attach the <strong>Shooter Mount<\/strong> using four 1 inch 8-32 bolts as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMounted.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMounted.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2005\" width=\"516\" height=\"476\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMounted.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMounted-300x277.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMounted-150x138.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/ShooterMounted-768x708.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 516px) 100vw, 516px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally zip-tie all of the cables to the tie holes a shown above.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, using a 8-32 tap, tap both ends of the two <strong>Feeder Supports<\/strong>:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"331\" height=\"243\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/FeederSupport-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2016\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/FeederSupport-1.jpg 331w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/FeederSupport-1-300x220.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/FeederSupport-1-150x110.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 331px) 100vw, 331px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Then attach the <strong>Feeder <\/strong>to the turntable using six 8-32 bolts as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Feeder.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"274\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Feeder-1024x274.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2017\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Feeder-1024x274.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Feeder-300x80.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Feeder-150x40.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Feeder-768x205.jpg 768w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Feeder-1536x411.jpg 1536w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Feeder.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now attach the <strong>Feeder Motor<\/strong> using two 4 mm M3 screws as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/FeederMotor.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/FeederMotor.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2021\" width=\"489\" height=\"379\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/FeederMotor.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/FeederMotor-300x233.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/FeederMotor-150x116.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/FeederMotor-768x596.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 489px) 100vw, 489px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next attach the <strong>6mm bore hex coupler<\/strong> to the <strong>Feeder Motor<\/strong> as shown below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/FeederCoupler.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/FeederCoupler.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2029\" width=\"484\" height=\"382\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/FeederCoupler.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/FeederCoupler-300x237.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/FeederCoupler-150x119.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/FeederCoupler-768x608.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 484px) 100vw, 484px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now glue the <strong>Flywheel Cap<\/strong> to the <strong>Flywheel <\/strong>using <strong>epoxy <\/strong>and after the glue has dried attach the two <strong>O-Rings<\/strong> as shown below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/Flywheel.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/Flywheel.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2392\" width=\"254\" height=\"231\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/Flywheel.jpg 876w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/Flywheel-300x273.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/Flywheel-150x136.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/Flywheel-768x698.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 254px) 100vw, 254px\" \/><\/a><figcaption>binary comment<\/figcaption><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>You may then want to balance the <strong>Flywheel<\/strong>. This can be done by inserting a 3mm rod through the center hole and then placing it between two supports to see how the wheel is balanced as shown below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/BalanceWheel.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2394\" width=\"443\" height=\"407\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/BalanceWheel.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/BalanceWheel-300x276.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/BalanceWheel-150x138.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/BalanceWheel-768x707.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 443px) 100vw, 443px\" \/><figcaption>binary comment<\/figcaption><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you have found the portion of the wheel which is heavier (it will rotate to the bottom) you can add extra material on the opposite side to balance the wheel. This material can consist of some additional epoxy glue, or in extreme cases you can glue on a small washer.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, attach the <strong>Flywheel <\/strong>to the <strong>Shooter Motor<\/strong> with a press fit as shown. Note that depending on your 3D printer the fit may be too tight or too loose. If it is too tight, drill out the hole in the Flywheel using a 3mm drill bit. If it is too loose, put a drop of glue from a <strong>hot glue<\/strong> gun on the hole of the <strong>Flywheel <\/strong>and immediately press it into position. Using <strong>hot glue<\/strong> instead of <strong>super glue<\/strong> will make it possible to remove the <strong>Flywheel <\/strong>later if needed.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/FlywheelMounte.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2397\" width=\"440\" height=\"356\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/FlywheelMounte.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/FlywheelMounte-300x243.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/FlywheelMounte-150x122.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/FlywheelMounte-768x623.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 440px) 100vw, 440px\" \/><figcaption>binary comment<\/figcaption><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now attach the<strong> Turntable Motor<\/strong> to the <strong>Turntable Motor Mount<\/strong> with two M3 screws as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/TurntableMotorMount.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/TurntableMotorMount.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2031\" width=\"483\" height=\"291\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/TurntableMotorMount.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/TurntableMotorMount-300x181.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/TurntableMotorMount-150x91.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/TurntableMotorMount-768x464.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 483px) 100vw, 483px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Then attach the <strong>Timing Belt Pully<\/strong>:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/TimingCoupler.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/TimingCoupler.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2034\" width=\"481\" height=\"303\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/TimingCoupler.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/TimingCoupler-300x190.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/TimingCoupler-150x95.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/TimingCoupler-768x485.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 481px) 100vw, 481px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, attach the <strong>Turret Motor Mount<\/strong> to the <strong>Chassis <\/strong>using two 8-32 bolts. Be sure to loop the timing belt around the <strong>Timing Belt Pully<\/strong> and adjust it so that the belt is taught but not tight. You should still be able to turn the turret an the belt should slip.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/TurretMotorAttached.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2037\" width=\"458\" height=\"270\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/TurretMotorAttached.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/TurretMotorAttached-300x178.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/TurretMotorAttached-150x89.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/TurretMotorAttached-768x455.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 458px) 100vw, 458px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally attach the <strong>Ball Hopper<\/strong> to the <strong>Turret <\/strong>using tape. Be sure to align the two edges as shown below. Positioning the <strong>Hopper <\/strong>in other orientations can lead to a situation where the ball can jam when rotating the feeder in either direction making it impossible to unjam.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/Hopper.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/Hopper-1024x464.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2386\" width=\"456\" height=\"207\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/Hopper-1024x464.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/Hopper-300x136.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/Hopper-150x68.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/Hopper-768x348.jpg 768w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/Hopper.jpg 1109w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 456px) 100vw, 456px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"\/final-assembly-and-wiring\/\">Next: Final Assembly and Wiring<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Attach the two Limit Switches to the top of the&nbsp;Turntable Bottom Plate&nbsp;using four 2-56 machine screws and four Limit Switch Spacers as shown below. Note the Limit Switch Spacers placed between the limit switch and the plate. Also pay attention to the orientation of the limit switches. Using the 4 Turntable Spacers, attach the&nbsp;Turntable Bering&nbsp;to&hellip;